I think you are looking for `profiles` in maven  . Look [here](http://maven.apache.org/guides/introduction/introduction-to-profiles.html) for more info

In your pom.xml , add `profiles` section and your `plugins` go into `&lt;pluginManagement&gt;` within `build` tag like below

      &lt;project xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0&quot; xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot; xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd&quot;&gt;
    
      &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;sourceDirectory&gt;src&lt;/sourceDirectory&gt;
        &lt;resources&gt;
          &lt;resource&gt;
            &lt;directory&gt;src&lt;/directory&gt;
            &lt;excludes&gt;
              &lt;exclude&gt;**/*.java&lt;/exclude&gt;
            &lt;/excludes&gt;
          &lt;/resource&gt;
        &lt;/resources&gt;
      
     &lt;pluginManagement&gt; 
    
     
         &lt;plugin&gt;
    			 &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    			 &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    			 &lt;version&gt;2.22.1&lt;/version&gt;
    
    			&lt;configuration&gt;
    						  &lt;suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    						  &lt;suiteXmlFile&gt;suite1.xml&lt;/suiteXmlFile&gt;
    						  &lt;/suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    					
    			&lt;/configuration&gt;
         &lt;/plugin&gt;
       &lt;/plugins&gt;
    	
     &lt;/pluginManagement&gt;  
    
       &lt;plugins&gt;
    		 &lt;plugin&gt;
    		 &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    		 &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    		 &lt;/plugin&gt;
    	 
       &lt;/plugins&gt;
    	
      &lt;/build&gt;
      
      
      
      &lt;profiles&gt; 
            &lt;profile&gt;
              
                &lt;id&gt;suite1&lt;/id&gt;
    
                &lt;build&gt;
                    &lt;plugins&gt;
                        &lt;plugin&gt;
                            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    
                             &lt;configuration&gt;
    								  &lt;suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    								  &lt;suiteXmlFile&gt;testng-customsuite.xml&lt;/suiteXmlFile&gt;
    								  &lt;/suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    							  
                             &lt;/configuration&gt;
                        &lt;/plugin&gt;
                    &lt;/plugins&gt;
                &lt;/build&gt;
            &lt;/profile&gt;
    		
    		 &lt;profile&gt;
               
                &lt;id&gt;suite2&lt;/id&gt;
                &lt;build&gt;
                    &lt;plugins&gt;
                        &lt;plugin&gt;
                            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    
                             &lt;configuration&gt;
    								  &lt;suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    								  &lt;suiteXmlFile&gt;suite2.xml&lt;/suiteXmlFile&gt;
    								  &lt;/suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    							 
                             &lt;/configuration&gt;
                        &lt;/plugin&gt;
                    &lt;/plugins&gt;
                &lt;/build&gt;
            &lt;/profile&gt;
        &lt;/profiles&gt;

    &lt;dependencies&gt; 
        ....
     &lt;/dependencies&gt;

Then based on `profiles` you can activate a `profile` like this from command line and then `suite` mentioned in that profile gets executed

`mvn clean test -P suite2`

Note that 
 
  `&lt;pluginManagement&gt;` - define plugins

  `&lt;plugins&gt;` - activate plugins

  `&lt;profile&gt;` - run suitable plugin based on what you pass in command line

These profile can also be activated through environment variables 

From above link  `Supported variables are system properties like ${user.home} and environment variables like ${env.HOME}`

EDIT:
  Have a look at [this](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48693617/maven-profile-activation-from-windows-system-variable-not-working) , This seems to suggest what you are trying to do may not be possible but you can try second solution . That is what I meant when I copy pasted above text from official site.

